description.plain:
One of the most popular EDM groups of the late 2010s and mainstays on Billboard’s Dance/Electronic charts, EDM/pop duo Cheat Codes consists of Trevor Dahl, Kevi Ford/PRINCE$$ ROSIE, Matthew Russell.

Formed in Los Angeles, California in 2014, the duo had their initial breakthrough in 2016 with the release of “Sex” with Dutch EDM trio Kris Kross Amsterdam. Sampling Salt-N-Pepa’s 1990 hit “Let’s Talk About Sex”, the song became a massive streaming hit and peaked at the #15 spot on the Billboard Bubbling Under Hot 100 chart. A year later, the trio entered the mainstream with the release of “No Promises”, featuring pop star Demi Lovato, amassing hundreds of millions of streams and breaking into the top 40 of the Hot 100, with the song peaking at #38.

In the years since, Cheat Codes has become a mainstay on the Dance charts, notching a total of 27 entries on Billboard’s Hot Dance/Electronic Songs chart and collaborating with artists across genres including Fetty Wap, AJ Mitchell, David Guetta, Little Mix, Bryce Vine, Tinashe, Kim Petras, All Time Low, Lee Brice, and Little Big Town.

description.plain:
“No Promises” is about the beginning of a relationship. It flows like a perfect summer club-banger.

The song marks the first release of 2017 for Demi Lovato and LA-based producer trio Cheat Codes.

It was first performed at the Beyond Wonderland Festival on March 24, 2017. Billboard tweeted about the song on March 25, 2017.

songs.full_title: Feels Great by Cheat Codes (Ft. CVBZ & Fetty Wap)
songs.title: Feels Great

description.plain:
Cheat Codes released “Feels Great”  in October 13th 2017. Cheat Codes collaborated with Fetty Wap for this electric dance trap influenced song about being young.

The American DJ trio told Billboard:

Fetty joining us on this song is the icing on the cake. We’re label partners with him and we played a show with him in Texas a few months back. This dude always has a smile on his face, so when we originally had the demo of the song we immediately thought he’d be perfect on it."

songs.full_title: Put Me Back Together by Cheat Codes (Ft. Kiiara)
songs.title: Put Me Back Together

description.plain: Breakout American singer Kiiara and production trio Cheat Codes unite for “Put Me Back Together.”  A sweet melody about the joys of having a better-half, the track is Cheat Codes' first release of 2018 and their first collaboration with Kiiara.
